{
  "stem": "15197.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Nevertheless, two people were smuggled out from the ghetto and one of them was Abraham Blum, one of the leaders.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And he didn't have a place where to go and he was located in mine apartment for the time being.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "We were looking for places-- how to help the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "But it was very difficult-- almost impossible.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And my feeling was, at that time, that everything really comes to an end.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "They tell to me that we have to go and to print some special poster from the Polish underground from the-- that the Jews are fighting for their freedom, for the ghetto, and from the Poles.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And the printing shop-- the illegal Polish printing shop-- was in [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "It was also on outskirt of Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "I took this-- this-- writing to the shop over there, but I have to go through-- alongside the Polish side of the ghetto wall and there were people staying there.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And the smoke was so dark, and flames from the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And I heard how people were talking.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "Oh, take a look.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "The Jews are frying.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "Or take a look, it's good that they came already to an end, that Warsaw will be liberated from Jews.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "It was a dangerous piece of walking distance to go.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "But nevertheless, I made it and I came back with the posters which has to be put up at night on the houses.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "When I brought to back the posters, two evenings later, in mine house with Abraham Blum, Gestapo-- a Gestapo person and a civilian came up and they closed the apartment.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "They took out everything and they found the Jews at Abraham.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "I didn't admit that I am Jewish.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "They took-- whatever it was valuable, they took.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And they told me that-- to remain there.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
